text: Xenambulacraria is a proposed clade of animals with bilateral symmetry as an embryo, consisting of the Xenacoelomorpha (i.e., Xenoturbella and acoelomorphs) and the Ambulacraria (i.e., echinoderms and hemichordates). They can be sister to the Nephrozoa (sans Ambulacraria), the Protostomes and Chordates. Xenambulacraria could also be sister to the Chordates File:Nemertodermatida species.png|Various Acoelomorpha (nemertodermatids).
